The paper deals with the computational complexity of modal dependence logic and its extensions, which are topics that are closely related to logic and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the classification of fragments of modal dependence logic, which is a problem that is related to computational complexity theory, and hence cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of the expressive power of different logics, which is a topic that is related to machine learning and statistical inference, and hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible sub-category.
